d ground-breaking applications Be the voice of Ripple\u2019s customers within the Ripple organization, ensuring that feedback and insights gained are proactively disseminated, inculcated, and acted upon by Ripple SUCCESS METRICS: Meet and exceed transaction corridor expansion targets Meet and exceed transaction volume targets for each customer Meet and exceed customer satisfaction and retention goals WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR: Embodiment of Ripple\u2019s Values known internally as \u201cLEGGOS\u201d - Live it, Enjoy it, Get it done, Go for it, Own it, and Say it 10+ years combined experience required in transaction banking, cash management, FX, payment processing, or a related field at a major financial institution in a customer-facing role Management consulting and delivery experience (or similar experience) gained within a technology or financial services organization Experience working in Fintech / Start-up organizations preferred Experience and cultural awareness with respect to working in and influencing cross-functional teams in a global enterprise Proven track record of implementing payment solutions within financial institutions Self-starter who is highly motivated to succeed in a challenging and rapidly changing business environment Results driven individual with determination and commitment to solving problems and getting things done Ability and willingness to travel 30% or more of the time Ability to credibly communicate and influence at the leadership level Professional proficiency in Spanish a plus Undergraduate degree or equivalent, MBA strongly preferred If you believe you are a strong fit for this role, please submit your resume for consideration. WHO WE ARE: Ripple provides one frictionless experience to send money globally using the power of blockchain. By joining Ripple\u2019s growing, global network (RippleNet), financial institutions can process their customers\u2019 payments anywhere in the world instantly, reliably and cost-effectively. Banks and payment providers can use the digital asset XRP to further reduce their costs and access new markets. With offices in San Francisco, New York, London, Mumbai, Singapore, S????????????o Paulo, Reykjav????????????k, Washington D.C. and Dubai, Ripple has more than 300 customers around the world. Ripple is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We\u2019re committed to building a diverse and inclusive team. We do not discriminate against qualified employees or applicants because of race, color, religion, gender identity, sex, sexual preference, sexual identity, pregnancy, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, marital status, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, military status, or any other characteristic protected by local law or ordinance. ", 
